        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Demi-Lich, while being a good upgrade, is a step a load of (modern) necros have bypassed due to the lack of long-term usage of it and inability to get a hold of it. Older necros (those who never seen that spell available before level 60) all lived through it with no big troubles.</P><P>While it is a good spell, remember you *will* stop to use it rather soon (ding 60!) - so i'd say, depending on your current level (and time it will take for you to get to 60), depending of the time it took you to save the money .. i would ask myself what is the long time best deal.</P><P>I dont mean here that demi-lich blows, it rocks (!)... But if you're leveling like mad and you estimate your level 60 to be in the next month or something, go for the earring ! The other way around, if you're not likely to get to level 60 in the next month or something, dont bother buying the earring and get that spell.</P><P>Nart.</P><P><BR>Edited by - Nartahs on 08/06/2002  10:06:56<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
