         Nalad - Why don't you join our ingame necro channel and ask the questions there?  </P><P>A couple reasons why I would choose earring over demi:</P><P>1.  Each of the Necros on our server has a "representative" on the MB team so we know when Demi drops, if ever, and more importantly who has it for sale.  Average price on TT is 25k.  Only reason one guy is selling for cheaper is because he asked me a PC and I said 5k.  He asked another Necro for PC and he also said 5k (we were in chat channel at the time collaberating prices, hehe).  That person then jacked price to 15k.  Druid anyone?</P><P>2.  With the exp rates being the way they are in Luclin, going from 55 to 60 is NO BIG DEAL without Demi Lich.  Sure it is an upgrade, blah blah blah.  You only use it for 4 levels.  Sure those levels are harder than any in the game, but you really aren't missing out on that much, especially when you get to 60.  At 60, demi will go to the back of your book.</P><P>3.  I never believed it until I saw the difference FT can make while soloing.  FT1 doesnt seem like a big deal at first, but in down time, fd it still works giving you an edge you didnt have before.  Plus the stats are nice as well.</P><P>Go with what you feel, but spending 15k+ for a spell for only 4 levels seems pointless to me.</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=134799" target="_blank"><img src="http://homepages.eq-guilds.com/ArchOfChaos/forums/images/quantic.jpg" border=0></a><BR><br><BR><font size=1>Warlock | <a href="http://www.archofchaos.com" target="_blank">Arch of Chaos</a><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
