         I still use demi lich over arch lich usualy.  The ratios on arch lich may be better theoreticly and it DOES give you 4 more mana per tick but each point of damage extra it does to me is damage over my regen so I actually don't think of the ratio as quite as good.  Of cource, that means lich has the best ratio because I lose no health... but let's be realistic here.  <img src=icon_smile.gif border=0 align=middle>  Arch lich will get you more mana in a shorter period of time but I'll just have to spend it to tap, anyways, makeing the net gain a small improvment.  Don't forget, arch lich is a huge model and it's a little more difficult to differentiate between sitting and standing while in spec form.  Skel form, while not impressive to newbies, is smaller and more practical as an actual model.  Slightly lower mana gain but reasonably less in the way of health loss.  I also heard an unconfirmed rumor that because of arch lich's size, it has more inturrupt issues due to you moving outside your box more easily when you get hit or something.</P><P>Anyways, get demi lich.  You might even find yourself using it at level 60 like me.  The only times I have been requested to use arch lich over demi lich is durring things like the ring of fire when people kinda like to have as few skeles arround as they can to help with quick targeting.</P><P><A href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=26159">Reegor</A> Mortees<BR>scaled Warlock<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
